		<div id="comment_body_64482977">Escape velocity is the velocity you need to escape the gravitational well without any additional energy being added. If you are in an orbit then you can alway add enough energy to escape (at least for classical systems). In the Earth-moon system the Earth is losing rotational energy to the moon which causes its orbit to raise.</div>
